AWARD-WINNING music producer and DJ Sandile Mkhize’s memorial service is underway in Soweto. It will take place at Pace Community Collegae in Jabulani, Soweto from 4pm. The DJ, best known by his stage name Citi Lyts, died on Monday, 14 February after an attempted hijacking. According to reports, he was ambushed and died on the scene after being shot eight times. The DJ became popular in 2015 with his single Washa, when he joined record label Ambitiouz Entertainment. ALSO READ | MUVHANGO'S JAMES IN TROUBLE He has worked with musicians Fifi Cooper, Sjava, B3nchmarq, LaSauce and Emtee. His brother, hip-hop star Prokid died in 2018 after suffering a severe seizure. The DJ’s death was confirmed to the People’s Paper by his dad Zwelakhe Kheswa, who said they were devastated but didn’t have much information about the incident. “He was executed. I don’t have any information about it now. We don’t want to make a mess with speculations.” Following the news of Citi Lyts’ passing, tributes have been pouring in for the fallen DJ, with many saying the music industry will not be the same without him.